review_blob: On tap at Oggis in Orange - small foamy head, light amber color, has a slight oak flavor in the hops.
On tap in orange. Sour acidic taste with an after taste just. As bad. Not a good version of an IPA.

Great gift from fellow boushy beer lover Travis, straight from Stone Brewery. 
Aroma is of apricots. Taste continues with apricot, with a creamy texture. Aftertaste fades smoothly leaving a slightly fruity film. Great beer!
Medium bodied IPA that has a grapefruit bitterness to it. Has a lingering dry finish. Not a great IPA.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Taste is very earthy with hints of pine. Finish lingers with bitter pine notes.
Aroma is citrus. Medium-light body.  Taste starts with citrus hops, but finishes with a bitter hop. Leaves a dry bitter finish.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Pours a deep reddish brown. Burnt sour aroma. Sour apple hops, with an increasing and lingering hoppy bitter finish.
beer_name: Port Brewing Shark Attack Double Red Ale

review_blob: Get the Idiot IPA by Coronado instead. This one is more bitter with a harsher finish. Not a bad IPA, but its idiot brother is better.
Inviting aroma. Starts with a citrusy spice flavor, with a strong hop body, finishing dry.

Very smooth for a double IPA, sweet hops, with a malty texture, medium bodied and a balanced finish. 
Great Beer!
Strong hops with a slight pine flavor, medium bodied, smooth lingering finish. Excellent IPA!
A light and refreshing IPA with a slight presence of hops, and a crisp finish! Overall, a nice beginners introduction to the world of IPAs.
